title: The Great Gatsby
author: F. Scott Fitzgerald
summary: The novel follows the disintegrating romance between the wealthy and socially awkward Jay Gatsby and his self-declared idealist, Daisy Buchanan.

title: To Kill a Mockingbird
author: Harper Lee
summary: A young girl learns about the injustices in her small Southern town by reading the diary of her father, Atticus Finch.

title: The Catcher in the Rye
author: J. D. Salinger
summary: Holden Caulfield, a disillusioned and dissociative teenager, is rebelling against the phoniness and phony behavior of his peers.

title: The Adventures of Huckleberry Finn
author: Mark Twain
summary: Huckleberry Finn, a boy growing up in the 19th century, is a typical 19th-century boy who is not afraid to speak his mind.

title: Alice's Adventures in Wonderland
author: Lewis Carroll
summary: Alice's Adventures in Wonderland is a classic novel that follows the journey of a young girl named Alice through various fantastical worlds.
